<h1 id=3D"APIComponentTestingGuidelines-Glossary:"><span style=3D"color: rg=
b(0,0,128);"><strong>Glossary:</strong></span></h1>
<p><a href=3D"/display/MESH/Glossary+for+How+to+Guides">Glossary for How to=
 Guides</a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1313874132">API Contract Testing Guidelines</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"f71de043-c5ca-40ac-9033-c26e502b=
fe11-1313874132">
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-IntendedAudienceforthisGuide:"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Intended Audience for this Guide:</=
strong></span></h1>
<p>Developer, Tester, Quality Engineer, Tech Lead</p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-UseCase:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
0,0,128);"><strong>Use Case:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<p>A developer or tester needs to automate API contract tests</p>
<p>Only applicable for Java API components at the moment</p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-BeforeyouStart:"><span style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Before you Start:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<ol>
<li>API Component must be created</li>
<li>Swagger design is completed</li>
<li>Component implementation to be in progress or complete</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-PurposeofContractTests:"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Purpose of Contract Tests:</strong></span=
></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">API Contract tests are required to=
 detect issues and consumer impacts at early stages.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">As a provider API, you must ensure=
 that changes to your component doesn't impact its consumers. Contract Test=
ing Serves the purpose to identify these issues.</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-INTRODUCTION"><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>INTRODUCTION</strong></span></h1>
<h5 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-WatchIntroductiontoContractTesting:A=
PIContractTestingIntroVideo"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Watch Int=
roduction to Contract Testing : <a href=3D"https://westpacgroup.sharepoint.=
com/:v:/r/sites/O365-UG-038487/Shared%20Documents/Mesh%20Learning%20series/=
QualityInMesh/API%20Contract%20Testing%20.mp4?csf=3D1&amp;web=3D1&amp;e=3DO=
FlN27" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">API Contract Testing Intro =
Video</a></span></h5>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-WhatisContractTesting:"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>What is Contract Testing:</strong></span>=
</h1>
<p>Contract testing&nbsp;is a technique for testing an integration point by=
 checking each application in isolation to ensure the response it sends or =
receives conform to a shared understanding that is documented in a "contrac=
t".</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">Contract testing is applicable any=
where you have two services that need to communicate - such as an API clien=
t and a web front-end. Although a single client and a single service is a c=
ommon use case, contract testing really shines in an environment with many =
services </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">(</span><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">as is common for a microservice architecture</sp=
an><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">)</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
28,30,33);">. Having well-formed contract tests makes it easy for developer=
s to avoid multiple versioning. Contract testing is the killer app for micr=
oservice development and deployment.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">In general, a contract is between =
a<span>&nbsp;</span><em>consumer</em><span>&nbsp;</span>(for example, a cli=
ent that wants to receive some data)<span>&nbsp;</span>and a<span>&nbsp;</s=
pan><em>provider</em><span>&nbsp;</span>(for example, an API on a server th=
at provides the data the client needs).</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ConsumerDrivenContractTesting:"><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Consumer Driven Contract Testing:<=
/strong></span></h3>
<p>An approach to contract testing that has consumers communicating their n=
eeds with the provider via a contract, and have the provider conform to the=
 superset of the needs of all of its consumers. <span style=3D"color: rgb(4=
8,54,51);">This in no way impacts on the fundamentally autonomous nature of=
 providers' implementations; it simply makes explicit the fact that service=
s depend for success on their being consumed.</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-FunctionalTestvsContractTest:"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Functional Test vs Contract Test:</=
strong></span></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Own=
er</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Functional Testin=
g</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Contract Testing<=
/p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Provid=
er</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>When I hit my req=
uest</p><p>Then I get successful response</p><p>And json.response message i=
s equal to "certain text"</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>When I hit the re=
quest</p><p>Then I get response object</p><p>And json response object match=
es with expected contract</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Consum=
er</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>When I hit my req=
uest&nbsp;</p><p>Then it consumes the provider's service</p><p>And&nbsp; I =
get the response</p><p>and response message is equal to "certain text"</p><=
p>and my function works as expected</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>When I hit the re=
quest</p><p>Then it consumes the provider's service</p><p>And I get the res=
ponse object And response object matches&nbsp;</p><p>with defined contract =
(e.g: json properties and its type and not the actual data)</p><p><br></p><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Exampl=
e</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><sp=
an class=3D"token plain">Response is 400 Bad Request</span><br><span class=
=3D"token plain">Response body is { "error": "username can only contain let=
ters" }</span></p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><sp=
an class=3D"token plain">Response is 400 Bad Request</span><br><span class=
=3D"token plain">Response body is { "error": "&lt;any string&gt;" }</span><=
/p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-AdvantagesofContractTestingoverFunct=
ionalTesting:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Advantages of C=
ontract Testing over Functional Testing:</strong></span></h3>
<p>Functional Testing conforms to the functional behaviour and hence it dep=
ends highly on data availability. Though we can use test doubles (stubs / m=
ocks), still there wont be any communication between provider and consumer =
and consumer can make use of provider mock without provider's consensus.&nb=
sp;</p>
<p>However, in contract testing there is not real data or environment depen=
dency when mocks are used and these mocks are agreed by both parties.&nbsp;=
</p>
<p>Note, For our MVP Phase: We support Contract testing against live enviro=
nment where in there is a data dependency involved.</p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-LibrarytoAutomateContractTests:"><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Library to Automate Contract Test=
s:</strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">We have chosen the Open source lib=
rary - <strong><em>PACT</em></strong> to automate API contract tests</span>=
</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">Note: PACT is language agnostic an=
d supports Java, Dotnet, NodeJS and much more.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);">Reference: <a href=3D"https://docs=
.pact.io/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.pact.io/</=
a></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(28,30,33);"><span class=3D"confluence-embedded=
-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-i=
mage-border" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"3ed6f7f58667b0b117ba31d69f93258f2fa=
