<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ConsumerPactTest:"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Consumer Pact Test:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(34,34,34);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Consumer PACT Test </span=
></span></span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);">&nbsp;is nothing but a Unit Test to test your pr=
ovider rest client using pact mock server instead of other libraries such a=
s mockito or powermock&nbsp;</span></span><p>Add the Pact Junit5 Consumer d=
ependency in your pom.xml</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">pom.xml dependency</b><span class=3D"collapse-sourc=
e expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-ico=
n icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</spa=
n></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht"> =09=09&lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;au.com.dius.pact.consumer&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit5&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;4.3.14&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div><p><br></p><p>Below is the example of the JUnit Test with Pact mock s=
erver against my provider meshDomainClient</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Consumer Junit Pact Test</b><span class=3D"collapse=
-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-contr=
ol-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand sourc=
e</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midni=
ght">package au.com.westpac.inf.bnkng.resrcitm.usraccsprof.meshusrperms.v1.=
restclient;

import au.com.dius.pact.consumer.dsl.PactDslJsonBody;
import au.com.dius.pact.consumer.dsl.PactDslWithProvider;
import au.com.dius.pact.consumer.junit5.PactConsumerTestExt;
import au.com.dius.pact.consumer.junit5.PactTestFor;
import au.com.dius.pact.core.model.PactSpecVersion;
import au.com.dius.pact.core.model.RequestResponsePact;
import au.com.dius.pact.core.model.annotations.Pact;
import au.com.westpac.inf.bnkng.busdrctnitm.dom.meshdom.v1.model.MeshDomain=
ListItem;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;
import org.springframework.test.context.ActiveProfiles;
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Objects;

@ActiveProfiles("test")
@SpringBootTest()
@ExtendWith(PactConsumerTestExt.class)
public class MeshDomainClientTest {

    @Autowired
    MeshDomainClient meshDomainClient;

    #Format of Provider and Consumer names should be same as the componentN=
ame defined in the component.yaml
    @Pact(provider =3D "inf-bnkng-busdrctnitm-dom-meshdom-v1", consumer =3D=
 "inf-bnkng-resrcitm-usraccsprof-meshusrperms-v1")
    RequestResponsePact retrieveDomains(PactDslWithProvider builder) {
        return builder
                .given("the mesh domains exists")
                .uponReceiving("request to get all mesh domains")
                .method("GET")
                .path("/inf/bnkng/busdrctnitm/dom/meshdom/v1/meshDomains/")
                .willRespondWith()
                .status(200)
                .body(new PactDslJsonBody().object("data")
                                                .minArrayLike("meshDomains"=
, 1)
                                                .stringType("meshDomainId",=
 "d0119")
                                                .stringType("domainName", "=
BankingPlatformDigital(BPD)")
                                .closeObject()
                        .closeArray())
                .toPact();
    }

    @Test
    @PactTestFor(pactMethod =3D "retrieveDomains", port=3D"9090", pactVersi=
on =3D PactSpecVersion.V3)
    void testGetMeshdomainSuccess() throws Exception {

        List&lt;MeshDomainListItem&gt; result =3D meshDomainClient.getMeshD=
omain();
        Assertions.assertNotNull(result);
        assertTrue(result.size()&gt;0);
        for(MeshDomainListItem item: result){
            assertTrue(item.getMeshDomainId().matches("^d[0-9a-f]{4}$"));
        }

    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,3=
4,34);">Every method under the client requires its unique RequestResponsePa=
ct to mock the response variations based on the test scenario</span></span>=
</p></li>
<li><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);">Format of Provider and Consume=
r names defined under Pact annotation in the RequestResponsePact should be =
same as the componentName defined in the component.yaml file</span></p></li=
>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>NOTE: For RestTemplate Spec=
ific</strong></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
If your code is based on WDPRestTemplate, please note just for Unit testing=
 - generic RestTemplate to be used since WDPRestTemplate by default redirec=
t to gateway url.</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
Below is the sample</span></span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">RestTemplateSpecific</b><span class=3D"collapse-sou=
rce expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-i=
con icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</s=
pan></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">## This could be your actual code where you are using WDPRestTemplate #=
#
@Bean
  @ConditionalOnProperty(havingValue =3D "false", value =3D "useSpringRestT=
emplate")
  public RestTemplate restTemplate(MappingJackson2HttpMessageConverter jack=
son2HttpMessageConverter) {
    SimpleClientHttpRequestFactory requestFactory =3D new SimpleClientHttpR=
equestFactory();
    requestFactory.setConnectTimeout(connectionTimeout);
    requestFactory.setReadTimeout(readTimeout);
    RestTemplate restTemplate =3D new WDPRestTemplate(requestFactory);
    restTemplate.setMessageConverters(List.of(jackson2HttpMessageConverter)=
);
    return restTemplate;
  }

## Below additional template with conditional property to be added for unit=
 testing purpose ##
@Bean
  @ConditionalOnProperty(havingValue =3D "true", value =3D "useSpringRestTe=
mplate")
  public RestTemplate testRestTemplate(MappingJackson2HttpMessageConverter =
jackson2HttpMessageConverter) {
    SimpleClientHttpRequestFactory requestFactory =3D new SimpleClientHttpR=
equestFactory();
    requestFactory.setConnectTimeout(connectionTimeout);
    requestFactory.setReadTimeout(readTimeout);
    RestTemplate restTemplate =3D new RestTemplate(requestFactory);
    restTemplate.setMessageConverters(List.of(jackson2HttpMessageConverter)=
);
    return restTemplate;
  }


## Also note in your src/test/resources/application.yaml below should be ad=
ded ##
useSprintRestTemplate: true</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ConsumerPACTTestRunviaIDE"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);"><strong>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);"=
><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Consumer PACT Test Run via IDE</span>=
</span></span></strong></span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,3=
4);">Run the above test similar to unit test in your local and ensure the t=
est passes.</span></span></li>
<li><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,3=
4,34);">Successful test run automatically generates the .json file under yo=
ur project/target/pacts directory for every consumer-provider combination a=
s below.&nbsp; This json file is called as Pact file or Contract file</span=
></span></p></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,3=
4);">Json name file would look like 'consumerName'-'providerName'.json e.g:=
 &nbsp;inf-bnkng-resrcitm-usraccsprof-meshusrperms-v1-inf-bnkng-busdrctnitm=
-dom-meshdom-v1.json</span></span></li>
<li>Name to be based on the above Provider and Consumer Names defined using=
 Pact annotation.=20
<ul>
<li>Note: Your provider component picks your json based on this consumer-pr=
ovider combination, hence it should strictly follow this format.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Sample : consumerName-providerName.json</b><span cl=
ass=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=
=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-te=
xt">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></s=
pan>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midni=
ght">{
  "consumer": {
    "name": "cap-technolsvcdsgndvlpmt-applnmgt-meshcmpntmgt-v1"
  },
