<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ConsumerPACTTestRunviaBuildPipeline"=
><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);=
"><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(3=
4,34,34);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Consumer PACT Test Run via =
Build Pipeline</span></span></span></strong></span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li>As part of the bamboo Build pipeline - above test runs as part of Unit =
testing and generates the .json files and these files (if exists) gets push=
ed to your build artifactory automatically. E.G: <a href=3D"https://artifac=
tory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifactory/wdp-001_MAVEN_snapshot/au/com/westpacgr=
oup/wdp/ipaas/api/cap/technolsvcdsgndvlpmt/applnmgt/meshcmpntmgt/v1/build/8=
48/pacts/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">build-pact-artifacts</a=
></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-Provider'sContractTest:"><strong><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Provider's Contract Test:</span></strong>=
</h2>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">Disclaimer</p><span class=3D"aui-icon =
aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Demo Video is recorded during MVP stage with Java example. It is only fo=
r high level understanding purpose. For any latest updates w.r.t version an=
d libraries always refer the below documented examples</p>
</div>
</div>
<h5 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-HowToForProvider:ProviderTestDemoVid=
eo"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">How To For Provider:&nbsp;<a href=
=3D"https://westpacgroup.sharepoint.com/:v:/r/sites/O365-UG-038487/Shared%2=
0Documents/Mesh%20Learning%20series/QualityInMesh/ProviderContractVerificat=
ioniMovie.mp4?csf=3D1&amp;web=3D1&amp;e=3D5NLiJc" class=3D"external-link" r=
el=3D"nofollow">Provider Test Demo Video</a></span></h5>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ProviderPactTest:"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Provider Pact Test:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(34,34,34);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Provider PACT Test </span=
></span></span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);">&nbsp;should be named as 'PactVerificationProvid=
erTest' under src/test/parent-package-contracttests similar to Unit test</s=
pan></span><p><br></p></li>
<li><p>Add the Pact Junit5 Provider dependency in your pom.xml</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">pom.xml dependency</b><span class=3D"collapse-sourc=
e expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-ico=
n icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</spa=
n></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht"> =09=09&lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;au.com.dius.pact.provider&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit5&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;4.3.14&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Below is the example of the Pact Provider Test for component 'inf-bn=
kng-resrcitm-usraccsprof-meshusrperms-v1'</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PactVerificationProviderTest.java</b><span class=3D=
"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"exp=
and-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Exp=
and source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midni=
ght">package au.com.westpac.inf.bnkng.resrcitm.usraccsprof.meshusrperms.v1.=
contracttests;

import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junit5.HttpsTestTarget;
import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junit5.PactVerificationContext;
import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junit5.PactVerificationInvocationContextPr=
ovider;
import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junitsupport.IgnoreMissingStateChange;
import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junitsupport.Provider;
import au.com.dius.pact.provider.junitsupport.loader.PactFolder;
import org.apache.hc.core5.http.HttpRequest;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.TestTemplate;
import org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;
import java.util.*;

#Provider Name should be same as componentName defined in your component.ya=
ml
@Provider("inf-bnkng-resrcitm-usraccsprof-meshusrperms-v1")
@PactFolder("pacts")
@IgnoreMissingStateChange
public class PactVerificationProviderTest {

    private static String hostname;


    private static int port;


    private static String apiKey;


    private static String apiSecret;

    @BeforeAll
    public static void loadProps() throws IOException {
        Properties properties =3D new Properties();
        properties.load(PactVerificationProviderTest.class.getClassLoader()=
.getResourceAsStream("application.properties"));
        hostname =3D properties.getProperty("mesh.hostname");
        port =3D Integer.parseInt(properties.getProperty("mesh.port"));
        apiKey =3D properties.getProperty("app-apiKey");
        apiSecret =3D properties.getProperty("app-apiSecret");
    }

    @BeforeEach
    final void before(PactVerificationContext context) throws Exception {
        //run against live environment
        HttpsTestTarget httpsTarget =3D new HttpsTestTarget(hostname, port)=
;
        context.setTarget(httpsTarget);

        //local run against mock
        //      HttpTestTarget httpTarget =3D new HttpTestTarget("localhost=
", 8080);
        //      context.setTarget(httpTarget);

    }

    @TestTemplate
    @ExtendWith(PactVerificationInvocationContextProvider.class)
    void test(PactVerificationContext context, HttpRequest request) {

        addHeaders(request);
        addBasicAuth(request);
        context.verifyInteraction();
    }

    private void addBasicAuth(HttpRequest request ){
        String auth =3D apiKey + ":" + apiSecret;
        byte[] encodedAuth =3D Base64.getEncoder().encode(auth.getBytes(Sta=
ndardCharsets.US_ASCII));
        String authHeader =3D "Basic " + new String( encodedAuth );
        request.addHeader("Authorization", authHeader);
    }

    private void addHeaders(HttpRequest request){
        //verify this condition is needed or not if consumer contract is pa=
ssing headers
        if (request.getHeaders().length=3D=3D0) {
            request.addHeader("accept", org.springframework.http.MediaType.=
APPLICATION_JSON.toString());
            request.addHeader("x-messageId", "ea19f949-c6ac-4c5c-8691-f3a0a=
3107042");
            request.addHeader("x-appCorrelationId", "035c364c-1582-4ef1-8c4=
f-d3b5fd8d1e8e");
            request.addHeader("x-organisationId", "WPAC");
            request.addHeader("x-originatingSystemId", "A00914");
            request.addHeader("x-consumerType", "Staff");
        }
    }

}

</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>Update pom.xml surefire-plugin to exclude PactProviderTest during Unit =
Test run.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
<li>Reasoning: Unit test run happens during Build pipeline and for MVP - Pa=
ct provider Test runs after deployment against live service, hence this tes=
t should be excluded during Build pipeline - Unit test run.</li>
<li>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Exclude Provider test for unit test run</b><span cl=
ass=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=
=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-te=
xt">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></s=
pan>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: xml; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">=09=09=09&lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;version&gt;2.22.0&lt;/version&gt;
                &lt;dependencies&gt;
                    &lt;dependency&gt;
                        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.platform&lt;/groupId&gt;
                        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-platform-surefire-provider&=
lt;/artifactId&gt;
                        &lt;version&gt;1.2.0&lt;/version&gt;
                    &lt;/dependency&gt;
                &lt;/dependencies&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;additionalClasspathElements&gt;
                        &lt;additionalClasspathElement&gt;src/test/java/&lt=
;/additionalClasspathElement&gt;
                    &lt;/additionalClasspathElements&gt;
                    &lt;excludes&gt;
                        &lt;exclude&gt;au/com/westpac/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/us=
raccsprof/meshusrperms/v1/contracttests/*.java&lt;/exclude&gt;
                    &lt;/excludes&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ProviderPACTTestRunviaIDE"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);"><strong>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);"=
><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Provider PACT Test Run via IDE</span>=
</span></span></strong></span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li>To run via IDE - create pacts folder under your root project folder and=
 place the relevant consumer pacts .json files (download from consumer buil=
d artifacts e.g: <a href=3D"https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifact=
ory/wdp-001_MAVEN_snapshot/au/com/westpacgroup/wdp/ipaas/api/cap/technolsvc=
dsgndvlpmt/applnmgt/meshcmpntmgt/v1/build/848/pacts/" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">build-pact-artifacts</a>)&nbsp; <em>#Do not commit thes=
e consumer pacts file</em></li>
<li><p>Create or Update application.properties under src/test/resources wit=
h following content <em>#Do not commit this file with apiKey apiSecret &amp=
; hostname actual values</em></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">application.properties</b><span class=3D"collapse-s=
ource expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control=
-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source<=
/span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midni=
ght"># Update all the values below while running PactVerificationProviderTe=
st via your IDE
app-apiKey=3Dapikey
app-apiSecret=3Dapisecret
mesh.hostname=3Dgwhostname
mesh.port=3D443</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>Right click on the test and click on Run test OR run via maven command =
in IDE terminal : mvn test -Dtest=3D"PactVerificationProviderTest"</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ProviderPACTTestRunviaPipeline"><spa=
n style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,34);"><st=
rong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,=
34);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">Provider PACT Test Run via Pipel=
ine</span></span></span></strong></span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Pipeline - Contract Test pipeline gets triggered automatically after ev=
ery successful deployment which downloads the json files from your consumer=
 build artifacts and executes the pact provider test against the deployed e=
nvironment.</li>
<li>Reference Pipeline links: <a href=3D"https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com=
.au/browse/WSP-APICONTRACTTEST-36" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/WSP-APICONTRACTTEST-36</a>&nb=
sp;</li>
</ul>
<p>Notifies the provider in case of test failures. If no consumer pacts fou=
nd, this build would pass for now.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">MVP Support Highlights</p><span class=
=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-information-mac=
ro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<ul>
<li>Pact provider Test is supported only with Junit5&nbsp;=20
<ul>
<li>Note: Pact do supports Junit4. However, our Contract testing Test conta=
iner is referring to the hardcoded pom.xml (inside the container) with depe=
ndency Junit5. This will get replaced with the actual pom.xml source in the=
 longer run.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Pact Provider Test is supported to run against only live environment an=
d not mocking (which in turn has a data dependency, expects the data to be =
available for the test to work successfully).&nbsp;=20
<ul>
<li>Note: Pact officially supports running only against Provider mock. As p=
er the customer request, we added the flexibility to support live environme=
nt run for MVP</li>
<li>In the longer run, Pact Provider states will be introduced to use mocke=
d response which in turn gets rid of data dependency</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-ContactsforassistancewithMeshEngagem=
entandServiceDeskTeams:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Conta=
cts for assistance with Mesh Engagement and Service Desk Teams:</strong></s=
pan></h1>
<ul>
<li>Mesh Engagement:&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:WDPEngagement@westpac.com.au" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">WDPEngagement@westpac.com.au</a></l=
i>
<li>Mesh Service Desk:&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:WDPSupport@westpac.com.au" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">WDPSupport@westpac.com.au</a></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIContractTestingGuidelines-Glossary:"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(0,0,128);"><strong>Glossary:</strong></span></h1>
<p><a href=3D"/display/MESH/Glossary+for+How+to+Guides">Glossary for How to=
 Guides</a></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1789178178">API TPIV in Prod</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"f71de043-c5ca-40ac-9033-c26e502b=
fe11-1789178178">
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-IntendedAudienceforthisGuide:"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Intended Audience for this Guide:</strong></span><=
/h1>
<p>Developer, Tester, Quality Engineer, Tech Lead, Application Owner</p>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-UseCase:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><str=
ong>Use Case:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<p>Mesh Component requires API TPIV (postman tests)&nbsp; following the Pro=
d deployment</p>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-BeforeyouStart:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128)=
;"><strong>Before you Start:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<ol>
<li>API Component implementation is complete</li>
<li>Prod TPIV required following API Component deployment (as part of Prod =
CRQ)</li>
<li>Access to Postman to create tests</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-PurposeofAPITPIVTests:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0=
,0,128);"><strong>Purpose of API TPIV Tests:</strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">API TPIV tests to run as part of T=
PIV Bamboo pipeline to ensure the successful validation following Prod depl=
oyment.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This pipeline can be triggered onl=
y by platform support team where there is a approved change task for TPIV a=
vailable in Prod CRQ</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">These tests are applicable for fol=
lowing component types:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">API</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Consuming Application</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">MFE</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Widget</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Stream Processor</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">As these are form of integration test=
s, you are allowed to call the component's dependencies directly and chain =
the requests within the same postman collection as long as the grant exist<=
/span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">e.g: Tests in microservice A can inc=
lude endpoints from both A and B microservices, provided that A depends on =
B and the appropriate grants are in place.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Though TPIV is applicable =
for above component types in Prod, it is highly encouraged to run your full=
 integration testing in the non prod environments referred here <a href=3D"=
/display/MESH/API+Integration+Testing+Guidelines">API Integration Testing G=
uidelines</a> and reduce the need of performing TPIV in Prod environment. <=
/span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Rather, Prod BPIV is recom=
mended to test the high level smoke tests via front end application.&nbsp;<=
/span></strong></p>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-TooltoAutomateAPITests:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
0,0,128);"><strong>Tool to Automate API Tests:</strong></span></h1>
<p>Open Source Version of Postman is used to script and test API endpoints.=
</p>
<p>Note: Use Postman lower version from<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"> =
<a href=3D"https://artifactory.srv.westpac.com.au/artifactory/chocolatey/un=
packaged/postman/9.31.30/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a=
> </span>and do not upgrade</p>
<h1 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-TPIVProcess"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,153);"=
><strong>TPIV Process</strong></span></h1>
<h3 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-Teststobecommitted:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,=
128);"><strong>Tests to be committed:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">TPIV test collection file should =
be named as 'integration_tests_postman_collection.json' and it should be co=
mmitted in the same dev code base repository </span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">ComponentType</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">api-tests folder</th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">API</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">./api-tests/prod1</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Consuming Application</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">./api-tests/prod1</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Stream Processor</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">./api-tests/prod1</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Listener</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">./api-tests/prod1</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">MFE</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>./api/api-tests/prod1</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Widget</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>./api/api-tests/prod1</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></li>
<li>Prod TPIV tests should be committed only under api-tests/prod1 folder a=
nd not under api-tests/default folder&nbsp;</li>
<li>Prod TPIV pipeline would pickup only the file from api-tests/prod1 fold=
er</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">It is the responsibility of Project =
teams to ensure that no sensitive data is present in the postman collection=
 file.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If the data is sensitive, a separate=
 encrypted data file must be added.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">data file should be named as integra=
tion_tests_postman_collection_data.json | csv (Please find the Postman data=
 file usage under Reference links)&nbsp;</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">It should be encrypted using dev-too=
ls mesh secrets command</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">mesh secrets command - generates the=
 data file with suffix -a.p7s and -b.p7s&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Only the encrypted data file to be c=
ommitted into the api-tests/prod1 folder</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Following the commit and merge to ma=
ster - API Build Pipeline publishes these tests into Artifactory under the =
corresponding Build number</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">During the Build pipeline - it also =
validates whether the postman collection exists and data file is encrypted.=
</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Any file other than idempotent_tests=
_postman_collection.json , integration_tests_postman_collection.json would =
fail the build.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Any data file other than encrypted f=
ile would fail the build validation.</span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-Teststobetestedinlowerenvironments:"><span style=3D=
"color: rgb(51,51,153);"><strong>Tests to be tested in lower environments:<=
/strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Have these same tests with non prod =
data tested as part of API Testing pipeline.&nbsp; Reference: <a href=3D"/d=
isplay/MESH/API+Integration+Testing+Guidelines">API Integration Testing Gui=
delines</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Make sure these tests are tested in =
non prod environments and it is successful </span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Save those non prod Test artefacts (=
to add in to Prod CRQ - change task later)</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Note: TPIV tests shouldn't be a full=
 blown integration testing. Ideally subset of non prod API integration test=
s becomes your TPIV</span></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-TPIVExecutionviaCI-TPIVPipeline:"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(51,51,153);"><strong>TPIV Execution via CI - TPIV Pipeline:</stron=
g></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Customers will not have access to ru=
n the Prod TPIV pipeline.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Customers to add the TPIV Change tas=
k as part of Prod CRQ. </span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Make sure the above tests are commit=
ted, built and tested in all non prod environments and the build number giv=
en in the Prod CRQ (for deployment) comprises these TPIV tests.</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Platform Support team triggers the T=
PIV pipeline based on the TPIV change task mentioned in the Prod CRQ.</span=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-ProdCRQChangesrelatedtoTPIV:"><span style=3D"color:=
 rgb(51,51,153);">Prod CRQ Changes related to TPIV:</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Add the Change Task specifically for=
 TPIV in the Prod CRQ</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Change Task title should be "Run TPI=
V Pipeline"</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Change Task description should be "R=
un TPIV Pipeline for component 'component name' prod test collection with b=
uild number"</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Attach the non prod integration test=
 artefact in the change task. </span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Provide the non prod bamboo test pip=
eline link - build number should match</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Attach the newman html report (previ=
ously downloaded from bamboo artefact)</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Get the SOM approval for the TPIV ch=
ange task.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Change implementation Plan to includ=
e the TPIV Run Request</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Run TPIV Pipeline for component 'com=
ponent name' prod test collection with build number</span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-SupportTeamGuideline"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0=
,128);"><strong>Support Team Guideline</strong></span></h2>
<h3 id=3D"APITPIVinProd-HowtoRun-TestPipeline:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0=
,0,128);"><strong>How to Run - Test Pipeline:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Prod TPIV Pipeline:&nbsp;<a href=3D"=
https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au/browse/WDPTESTPROD1-APITESTPROD1" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bamboo-wdp.srv.westpac.com.au=
/browse/WDPTESTPROD1-APITESTPROD1</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">API Integration Test Pipeline to be =
triggered as Custom Run - passing the API <strong>REPO_NAME </strong>or<str=
ong> COMPONENT_NAME and COMPONENT_TYPE </strong>and the<strong> BUILD_NUMBE=
R</strong></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong><span class=3D"confluence-emb=
edded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border" draggable=3D"false" width=
