span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-UpdatethelibraryversioninAPI-JavaAPI"><sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Update the library version in API=
 - Java API</strong></span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Checkout you API code repository (you=
r API "X" from above scenario) in your local</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Update the wdp-helpers version to 0.0=
.28 under dependencies in pom.xml</span></p>
<pre><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&lt;dependency&gt;<br></span>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">  &lt;groupId&gt;</span>au.com.wes=
tpac.wdp.commons.westpac.digital.platform<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,=
106);">&lt;/groupId&gt;<br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">=
  &lt;artifactId&gt;</span>wdp-helpers<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106=
);">&lt;/artifactId&gt;<br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">=
  &lt;version&gt;</span>0.0.28<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&lt;=
/version&gt;<br>  &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;<br></span><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&lt;/dependency&gt;<br></span></pre>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Update the tomcat-support version to =
0.0.30 under dependencies in pom.xml - <em>only if you want to debug the co=
de in local to see how mockoon redirection works via WDPContext class</em><=
/span></p>
<pre><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&lt;dependency&gt;<br></span>=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">  &lt;groupId&gt;</span>au.com.wes=
tpac.wdp.commons.westpac.digital.platform<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,=
106);">&lt;/groupId&gt;<br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">=
  &lt;artifactId&gt;</span>tomcat-support<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,=
106);">&lt;/artifactId&gt;<br></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106)=
;">  &lt;version&gt;</span>0.0.30<span style=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&=
lt;/version&gt;<br>  &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;<br></span><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(232,191,106);">&lt;/dependency&gt;</span></pre>
<h3 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-StartyourAPIviameshrun"><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Start your API via mesh run</strong></span></h3=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102)=
;">'<em>mesh run</em>' command is used to run your api instance in local</s=
pan></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102)=
;">In order to make this command work, you need to have the <a href=3D"http=
s://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D=
"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a> installed</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102)=
;">If you don't have this set up already follow the instructions from here =
to install <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Me=
sh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a></span></span>=
</p>
<p><strong><em>pip list | grep "wdp-dev-tools"</em></strong> should display=
 the wdp-dev-tools version 1.13.0 or above</p>
<p>Make sure you have the necessary secrets, config, or datastore setup in =
your local for the api to be up and running</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Get into directory of your API project root folder in a command prompt o=
r terminal</p>
<p>Do: '<em><strong>mesh run -m True</strong>'</em></p>
<p>Reference:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display=
/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">mesh run command</a></p>
<p>Above commands starts the api instance in local pointing to mock server =
localhost:3010</p>
<p><br></p>
