ia Postman in systemTest mode</strong></span></h3>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-b=
order" draggable=3D"false" width=3D"468" src=3D"cfccd0a8f5a1f9aae9bfea4b8a5=
9e148bd3255e1972e890c2a98fb680c6882fa" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachme=
nts/1557945143/image-2023-12-4_16-32-11.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDat=
e=3D1701667931583&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-li=
nked-resource-id=3D"1557949734" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-lin=
ked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"imag=
e-2023-12-4_16-32-11.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.c=
om.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource=
-container-id=3D"1557945143" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"39" =
alt=3D"" height=3D"180"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-Howitworksinlocal"><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>How it works in local</strong></span></h3>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">When you hit api with x-systemTest header set to <em>true</em></span></=
span><em><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,5=
1,102);">&nbsp;</span></span></em>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">Your api points to your local mockoon instance localhost:3010 via wdp-h=
elper</span></span></li>
</ol></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">When you hit your api without x-systemTest header</span></span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">Your api points to real gateway dependent api</span></span></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-IntegratewithMockoonviaDeploymentPipeline=
forAPIs:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Integrate with Mocko=
on via Deployment Pipeline for APIs:</strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-SCENARIO:.2"><strong><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,128);">SCENARIO:</span></strong></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>GIVEN</strong> <span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">I am the API or MFE owner (developer or tester) of =
"X"</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>AND</strong> <span style=3D=
"color: rgb(0,0,0);">"X" is dependent on other api "Y"</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>WHEN</strong>&nbsp;</span><=
span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">my mockoon mocks are created for "Y", tes=
ted api "X" in local instance pointing to "Y" mocks and ready to get deploy=
ed</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>THEN&nbsp;</strong><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">during deployment of "X", mockoon container gets=
 started as test-sidecar container within the API deployment K8s pod</span>=
</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>AND</strong></span> I can test=
 my component "X" in systemTest mode&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-StepstoIntegrate:"><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Steps to Integrate:</strong></span></h3>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Once Mocks are ready to be deployed,=
 rename your mock file as mockoon-data.json and push to your code repositor=
y - env/default folder or env/dev1 or env/{envname) </span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Build your component with above comm=
it</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Deploy your component with above bui=
ld number via deployment pipeline</span></li>
</ol>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-TestyourAPI&quot;X&quot;viapostmaninsyste=
mTestmode"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Test your API "X" v=
ia postman in systemTest mode</strong></span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong><span class=3D"confluence-e=
mbedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"conflue=
nce-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border" draggable=3D"false" wid=
th=3D"468" src=3D"b0fe079d2a658a019fac029c4441f405b124d2782733bd28661209cec=
6f9784d" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1557945143/image-2023-12-4=
_18-25-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1701674739917&amp;api=3Dv2=
" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1557950645=
" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachmen=
t" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-2023-12-4_18-25-39.png" data=
-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-co=
ntent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1557945143" d=
ata-linked-resource-container-version=3D"39" alt=3D"" height=3D"177"></span=
></strong></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-Howitworksinpipeline"><span style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>How it works in pipeline</strong></span></h1>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">When api is deployed with mockoon-data.json + deployment pipeline start=
s with "<s>ENABLE_SERVICE_VIRTUALIZATION</s>" "ENABLE_COMPONENT_TESTS" set =
to true</span></span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">Deployment pipeline starts the mockoon container as test-sidecar </span=
></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">Within the Mockoon container - it starts the mockoon cli server pointin=
g to above mockoon-data.json in localhost: port 3010</span></span></li>
</ol></li>
<li>"<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,10=
2);"><s>ENABLE_SERVICE_VIRTUALIZATION</s>" "<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,1=
28);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">ENABLE_COMPONENT_TESTS" </span>=
</span>variable in deployment pipeline - default is set to true only in dev=
1. In other environments - this variable is defaulted to false</span></span=
></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">If you want to deploy api with mocks in SIT1 and above non-prod environ=
ments</span></span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">Do the Custom Run of your deployment pipeline overriding the variable "=
<s>ENABLE_SERVICE_VIRTUALIZATION</s>" "<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"=
><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">ENABLE_COMPONENT_TESTS" </span></spa=
n>to True</span></span></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102)=
;">Note: <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,5=
1,102);"><s>ENABLE_SERVICE_VIRTUALIZATION </s> has been renamed to in platf=
orm 2.15 release </span></span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">ENABLE_COMPONENT_TESTS</span></span></span><=
/span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-ThingstoKnow"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0=
,0,128);"><strong>Things to Know</strong></span></h1>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">When you hit your api with x-systemTest set to true =E2=80=93 wdp-helpe=
r&nbsp; redirects all the underlying dependent api (upstream / downstream) =
calls to localhost:3010 instead of gateway url.</span></span>
<ol>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">If the dependent api mocked - it fetches the response from the mocked e=
ndpoint</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">If the dependent api is not mocked - it redirects the call back to resp=
ective gateway url (using Mockoon's proxy redirection feature)</span></span=
></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">As Mockoon supports the proxy redirection - if the endpoint route is no=
t matched, it redirects the call to gateway url. Hence it is not required t=
o mock all your dependent apis. </span></span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">If "X" is dependent on Y and Z , you can mock only Y and with proxy red=
irection feature Z calls gets redirected to gateway endpoints.</span></span=
></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">If "X" is dependent on Y, you can mock few endpoints of Y and with prox=
y redirection feature non-mocked endpoint gets redirected to gateway url.</=
span></span></li>
</ul></li>
</ol></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102=
);">When you hit your api without x-systemTest - all the underlying depende=
nt api calls goes to gateway url as usual.</span></span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102)=
;">Hence, your component can be tested with or without mocks at the same ti=
me without changing any configuration and without any redeployment.</span><=
/span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-MFEorUIIntegrationwithMockoon"><span styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>MFE or UI Integration with Mockoon</stro=
ng></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">All the above guides are common for M=
esh UI components as the Mockoon container setup and the platform deploymen=
t stages are common for both apis and ui components.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The only difference is the folder str=
ucture where the mockoon-data.json to be placed and the way it gets called =
by UI are different.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Refer the confluence from here for MF=
E or UI Mockoon integration: <a href=3D"/display/MESH/Setup+mockoon+service=
+virtualisation+on+Mesh+UI">Setup mockoon service virtualisation on Mesh UI=
</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIVirtualizationinMesh-GuildSessionRecording"><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Guild Session Recording</strong></span></h1>
