<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-IntendedAudienceforthisGuide:"><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Intended Audience for this Guide:</s=
trong></span></h1>
<p>Developer, Tester, Quality Engineer, Tech Lead</p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-UseCase:"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0=
,0,128);"><strong>Use Case:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<p>A developer or tester needs to automate idempotent tests for API compone=
nt via Postman</p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-BeforeyouStart:"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Before you Start:&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<ol>
<li>API Component must be created</li>
<li>Swagger design is complete</li>
<li>Component implementation to be in progress or complete</li>
<li>Access to Postman</li>
</ol>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-PurposeofIdempotentTests:"><span styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Purpose of Idempotent Tests:</strong></s=
pan></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Idempotent tests to run automatica=
lly as part of the deployment Bamboo pipeline to ensure successful deployme=
nt.</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-WhatisanIdempotentAPITest:"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>What is an Idempotent API Test:</strong=
></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Idempotency<span style=3D"color: r=
gb(34,34,34);">&nbsp;means that the result of a successfully performed requ=
est is independent of the number of times it is executed.</span></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-IdempotencywithHTTPMethods:"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Idempotency with HTTP Methods:</strong=
></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(34,34,34);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);">HTTP GET</span>&nbsp;</sp=
an></span></strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(34,34,34);">methods never change the resource state on the server. =
They are purely for retrieving the resource representation or metadata at t=
hat point in time.</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(34,34,3=
4);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>HTTP PUT</strong></span> =
- PUT APIs are used to update the resource state. If we invoke a PUT API N =
time, the very first request will update the resource, the other N-1 reques=
ts will just overwrite the same resource state again and again - effectivel=
y not changing anything. Hence PUT is idempotent.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-TooltoAutomateIdempotentTests:"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Tool to Automate Idempotent Tests:<=
/strong></span></h1>
<p>Open Source Version of Postman is used to script and test Idempotent API=
 Methods</p>
<h3 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-Teststobecommitted:"><span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Tests to be committed:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Idempotent test collection file shou=
ld be named as 'idempotent_tests_postman_collection.json' and it should be =
committed in the same dev code base repository under the project root direc=
tory ./api-tests/default</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">If the test varies between environme=
nts then respective env folder to be created and seperate collection to be =
placed underneath.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Default tests would run against all =
envs and tests under respective env folder would run only against those env=
ironments during deploy pipeline</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-GuidelinesforGoodIdempotentTests:"><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Guidelines for Good Idempotent T=
ests:</strong></span></h1>
<ul>
<li>Create a collection and write Postman tests for all Get and PUT request=
s</li>
<li>If the endpoint has mandatory query parameters, there should be a valid=
 test for that endpoint with required query parameters</li>
<li>If the endpoint has path parameters, then the test should have a valid =
endpoint with path parameter value (either as hard coded value or as a vari=
able)<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Test with PathParam as global variable</b><span cla=
ss=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=
=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-te=
xt">Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></s=
pan>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">"url": {
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"raw": "{{hostname}}/inf/bnkng/resrcitm/logclitcmpnt/w=
dpcatlg/v1/environments/{{env}}/components/deployments?componentType=3Dapi&=
amp;pageKey=3D1",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"host": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"{{hostname}}"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09],
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"path": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"inf",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"bnkng",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"resrcitm",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"logclitcmpnt",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"wdpcatlg",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"v1",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"environments",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"{{env}}",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"components",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"deployments"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09],
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"query": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09{
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"key": "componentType",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"value": "api"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09},
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09{
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"key": "pageKey",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"value": "1"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09}
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09]
=09=09=09=09=09=09}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Test with PathParam as local variable</b><span clas=
s=3D"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D=
"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text"=
>Expand source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span=
>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">"url": {
=09=09=09=09=09=09"raw": "{{hostname}}/inf/bnkng/busdrctnitm/dom/meshdom/v1=
/meshDomains/:meshDomainId",
=09=09=09=09=09=09"host": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"{{hostname}}"
=09=09=09=09=09=09],
=09=09=09=09=09=09"path": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"inf",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"bnkng",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"busdrctnitm",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"dom",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"meshdom",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"v1",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"meshDomains",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09":meshDomainId"
=09=09=09=09=09=09],
=09=09=09=09=09=09"variable": [{
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"key": "meshDomainId",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"value": "d0890",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"description": "(Required) Unique identifier for the M=
esh Domain"
=09=09=09=09=09=09}]
=09=09=09=09=09}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>Each test should follow with proper assertion statements.</li>
<li>Assertions should exist for both response status code and response mess=
age as well.</li>
<li>Assertions should follow appropriate pattern=20
<ul>
<li>e.g. responseCode.code <strong>=3D=3D=3D</strong> 200 and <strong><em>d=
o&nbsp;not&nbsp;use</em>&nbsp;</strong>responseCode.code<strong>&nbsp;!=3D=
=3D</strong> 500&nbsp;</li>
<li><p>Try to always assert with expected value.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Good Test Example</b><span class=3D"collapse-source=
 expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon=
 icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span=
></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">"script": {
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"exec": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"if (responseCode.code =3D=3D=3D 200) {\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"    tests[\"Status code is 200\"] =3D true;\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"    var jsonData =3D JSON.parse(responseBody);\=
r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"    tests[\"Result is non-empty\"] =3D jsonData=
.data.idempotentTestCoverages.length =3D=3D=3D 0;\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"}\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"else {\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"    tests[\"expected at least one result for /i=
dempotentTestCoverages\"] =3D false;\r",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"}"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09],
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"type": "text/javascript"
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>&nbsp;<em><strong>!=3D=3D</strong> 500 <strong>would pass irrespecti=
ve of actual status code</strong> 200, 400, 401, 404 , etc.. and <strong>he=
nce this is considered as bad test</strong></em></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Bad Test example</b><span class=3D"collapse-source =
expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon =
icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span>=
</span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnigh=
t">"script": {
=09=09=09=09=09=09"type": "text/javascript",
=09=09=09=09=09=09"exec": [
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"if(responseCode.code !=3D=3D 500){",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"tests[\"Status code is 200\"] =3D true;",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"var jsonData =3D JSON.parse(responseBody);",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"tests[\"Status is success\"] =3D (jsonData.status =3D=
=3D=3D \"success\") || (jsonData.type =3D=3D=3D \"ok\");",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"}",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"else{",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"    tests[\"Status Code is: \"+responseCode.code] =3D=
 false;",
=09=09=09=09=09=09=09"}"
=09=09=09=09=09=09]
=09=09=09=09=09}</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<ul>
<li>Consider adding tests around some of the negative scenarios .&nbsp;=20
<ul>
<li>e.g. Invalid componentId - Expected to return 200 with empty string.&nb=
sp;</li>
<li>e.g. Missing Header - Expected to return 400 with valid error message</=
li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-MESHCONNECTPortaldisplaysOverallTestS=
core"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>MESH CONNECT Portal disp=
lays Overall Test Score</strong></span></h1>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Your Idempotent and non-idempotent Te=
st Coverage gets displayed in Mesh Connect against your component in Qualit=
y tab as below:</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-b=
order" draggable=3D"false" width=3D"468" src=3D"13de67270dd2d97fbcc17d6a826=
88d08c591eedff546e82cff3c83e5f9b3ef3c" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachme=
nts/1203279638/image-2024-9-5_16-49-31.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=
=3D1725518971273&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-lin=
ked-resource-id=3D"1824103869" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-link=
ed-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image=
-2024-9-5_16-49-31.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com=
.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-c=
ontainer-id=3D"1203279638" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"11" al=
t=3D"" height=3D"170"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"IdempotentAPITestGuidelines-TestCoverageScoreCalculationLogic:"><=
span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,128);"><strong>Test Coverage Score Calculation=
 Logic:</strong></span></h1>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Swagger / Openapi is considered as=
 the source of truth for expected idempotent tests. </span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">The test:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">For Idempotent: Grabs&nbsp;<stron=
g>all the GET &amp; PUT operations</strong>&nbsp;(including parameter combi=
nations) from the respective <strong>contract</strong> file =3D=3D&gt; <em>=
<strong>expected_count'</strong></em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">For Non Idempotent: Grabs all the=
 other operations other than GET &amp; PUT (including parameter combination=
s)&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">from the respective <strong>c=
ontract</strong> file =3D=3D&gt; <em><strong>expected_count'</strong></em><=
/span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Grabs all the postman tests from =
the repository / api-tests directory - both default and all the environment=
s folder</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Removes any duplicates if same te=
st is present in multiple environment folder (for MVP )</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Compares the expected swagger/ope=
napi operation against the postman test operations</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">If the<strong> valid operation</s=
trong> is present once or more <strong>in the postman test collection</stro=
ng> and if the assertion statement doesn't have the bad code pattern (e.g. =
responseCode.code!=3D=3D) it will be counted as one test for <em><strong>ac=
tual_count</strong></em></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">If the valid operation (including=
 required path parameter and/or mandatory query parameter) is not present e=
ven once then it will not be counted.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">If the valid operation is present=
 and if the assertion is found as bad assertion then it will not be counted=
 in.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Coverage score =3D (actual=
_count / expected_count) * 100</span></strong></p>
<p><br></p>
